.TH "nfp_xpb_writelm" 9 "nfp_xpb_writelm" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
nfp_xpb_writelm \- Modify bits of a 32-bit value from the XPB bus
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" nfp_xpb_writelm
.BI "(struct nfp_cpp *cpp "  ","
.BI "u32 xpb_tgt "  ","
.BI "u32 mask "  ","
.BI "u32 value "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "cpp" 12
NFP CPP device handle
.IP "xpb_tgt" 12
XPB target and address
.IP "mask" 12
mask of bits to alter
.IP "value" 12
value to modify
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
KERNEL: This operation is safe to call in interrupt or softirq context.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, or -ERRNO
